8	 * verify -> adjudicate; C-079). Every candidate it emits carries a deterministic artifact (Rule 3): a
9	 * verbatim quote string-matched to the corpus, a captured browser event, a definitive register-lane
10	 * fact, or a coverage proof. No artifact, no candidate.
11	 *
12	 * ── how each evidence_type routes ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
13	 *   presence   (REQUIRED content)  -> ABSENCE-breach: the required pattern is ABSENT across the covered,
14	 *                                     declared surface. Fires only with the coverage interlock proven
15	 *                                     (record covered, corpus not truncated, >= the min-pages floor,
16	 *                                     surface readable). Artifact: coverage_proof. confidence: moderate.
17	 *   absence    (PROHIBITED content)-> PRESENCE-breach: the prohibited pattern is FOUND inside one visible
18	 *                                     prose sentence that is neither negated (the site's own compliant
19	 *                                     self-declaration, C-048) nor a customer review (C-090). Artifact:
