2	// eval/e2e/lib/redteam.js - the red-team lane (docs/P3-ACCEPTANCE.md wave 3, caution.md C-165):
3	// adversarial fixtures that try to make the engine fabricate. ABSENCE of eval/red-team/fixtures.json
4	// is handled as an honest, whole-lane skip (never a fabricated pass on zero entries - the same C-037
5	// doctrine as a skipped breach stage).
6	//
7	// eval/red-team/fixtures.json landed mid-build with a richer, per-fixture-bespoke shape than a single
8	// generic contract can fully express (nine adversarial classes, RT-A through RT-H; see its own
9	// `doctrine`/`bundle_shape_ref` blocks). This module supports it in two layers:
10	//
11	//   1. BESPOKE per-id handlers (eval/e2e/lib/redteam-handlers.js) for the entries whose `input` is not
12	//      a plain crawl-shaped EvidenceBundle (RT-D: fetch + honest/naive bundle; RT-G: cookies +
13	//      browser_script; RT-H: bare corpus strings), or whose correct handling needs xfail semantics
14	//      (RT-F: a known, already-tracked escape). An id with a bespoke handler is dispatched there first.
15	//   2. A GENERIC evaluator for everything else: resolve a runnable EvidenceBundle from the entry
16	//      (`entry.input.bundle`, or this file's own originally-documented `entry.bundle`/`entry.fixture`/
17	//      `entry.domain` shapes, kept for forward compatibility), run it through the real pipeline, and
18	//      check every STRING value (and every string inside an array value) anywhere in `entry.must_not`
19	//      as a forbidden token against the pipeline's findings and its whole serialised output. Boolean
20	//      flags (most of this file's `must_not` clauses - e.g. RT-B1/RT-B2/RT-E are ENTIRELY boolean
21	//      flags describing a behavioural invariant) carry no searchable text and so contribute nothing:
22	//      those entries fall through to an honest 'skipped', never a fabricated 'caught' on a check that
23	//      never actually ran.
24	//
25	// `target_gate` in the real file is an object ({gate, status, ...}), not a bare stage name; this file's
26	// ORIGINAL assumed contract (a bare string naming one of this harness's own stage names) is still
27	// checked as a harmless, forward-compatible fallback, but the real file's own `current_status`/
28	// `target_gate.status === 'pending_gate'` (the gate does not exist on disk at all) is the primary,
29	// authoritative "skip this, it cannot be evaluated yet" signal, read directly from the fixture's own
30	// declared truth rather than guessed.
